  "description": "<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<p>This is a TRUE SLOT CANYON in the southeast. While it is not as\nserious as most of the canyons out west, this is not a place for\nbeginners. You should not enter this canyon until you understand how to\ninspect and replace anchors, until you are competent at rappelling, and\nit is preferred that you know how to build a contingency anchor and that\nyou know how to ghost anchors. If you get hurt or stuck in this canyon,\nSAR will have a hard time getting you out.</p>\n<p>While this canyon is getting more and more traffic, it is still not\nrun extremely often. You should be prepared to replace anchors (bring\n~30 ft webbing for sure and preferably a couple of quick links). It is\npreferred to use black webbing as photographers will hike up from the\nbottom to photograph the falls, and would probably get annoyed if there\nis a bright orange piece of webbing at the top of the falls. Since this\nis a location that people have historically bushwhacked up to, it is\ngood practice to ghost all the rappels that are not ghosted. However,\nthis is absolutely not the place to learn how to do that. If you need to\nleave anchors behind, please use black webbing. Keep this in mind, as if\nyou need anchors placed, you should not come expecting them to be here\n(plan to bring webbing and quick links)</p>\n<p>Things you should know before entering this canyon:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How to rappel single strand</li>\n<li>How to give a fireman's belay</li>\n<li>How to communicate with a whistle or hand signals (communicating\nover 1000 ft with a waterfall between you can be challenging with your\nvoice)</li>\n<li>How to set a biner block, and preferably how to set a contingency\nanchor (figure 8 block, macrame, etc.)</li>\n<li>How to add or remove friction from your rappel device mid rappel\n(Canyoneering specific devices such as the Imlay Critr, Sterling ATC, or\nBG Sqwurel make this exceptionally easy compared to climbing and caving\ndevices)</li>\n<li>How determine if an anchor is good enough (tree diameter, root\nstructure, location compared to rappel, etc.)</li>\n<li>How to build an anchor (how to tie a water knot, how to keep webbing\nat desired height, etc.)</li>\n<li>How to self-rescue (how to lower a stuck rappeler, how to ascend\nback up a rope, how to lower a hurt member of the party, etc.)</li>\n<li>Simple first aid - It is a pretty easy place for someone to get\nhurt, the rock is slick, the creek walk would be an easy place for\nsomeone to break an ankle, almost everyone I have been with has fallen\nat some point or another during the trips, and you do not have service\nto call for help so it is best to be able to do simple first aid to be\nable to get someone who is hurt back to the car.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"approach\">Approach</h2>\n<p>Hike up the Bartram Trail. You gain just over 1,000 feet in 1.5\nmiles. Once the trail meets up with the creek, you can put on your\nwetsuit (if wearing one). Then you will turn and follow the stream for\n0.5 miles until you see the slot section.</p>\n<h2 id=\"descent\">Descent</h2>\n<p><strong>Before the Falls</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>S1: 8 ft</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Notch Falls</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>R0: 10 ft off tree DCL (you can also downclimb this section pretty\neasily)</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>R1: 20 ft off two bolts DCL</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>R2: 50 ft off two bolts DCR (two stage rappel with a 6 foot swim\nbetween them)</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Ledbetter Canyon Falls</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>R3: 75 ft off tree DCL (Option 1: Straight down the gully not in\nwater. Option 2: go right and use boulder as a redirect and go in the\nwater *recommended*)</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>R4: 75 ft off two bolts DCR</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>R5: 90 ft off tree DCL</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 id=\"exit\">Exit</h2>\n<p>Follow the creek ~0.75 miles until it goes under a bridge. You car\nwill be about 20 feet after the bridge. You can also hop back on the\nBartram trail about 0.25 miles sooner and take that back to the parking\narea.</p>\n<h2 id=\"red_tape\">Red tape</h2>\n<h2 id=\"beta_sites\">Beta sites</h2>\n<p><a\nhref=\"https://gaeaphotos.com/rappelling-the-notch-a-true-nc-slot-canyon/\">https://gaeaphotos.com/rappelling-the-notch-a-true-nc-slot-canyon/</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media</h2>\n<h2 id=\"background\">Background</h2>\n",
